SIMPLE: seesaw
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seesaw
<hw>See"saw`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably a
reduplication of <ets>saw</ets>, to express the alternate motion to and
fro, as in the act of sawing.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A play among
children in which they are seated upon the opposite ends of a plank
which is balanced in the middle, and move alternately up and
down.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A plank or board adjusted for this play.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A vibratory or reciprocating motion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He has been arguing in a circle; there is thus a <qex>seesaw</qex>
between the hypothesis and fact.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Whist.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Crossruff</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seesaw</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Seesaw
<hw>See"saw`</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Seesawad</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Seesawing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To move with a reciprocating
motion; to move backward and forward, or upward and downward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seesaw</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Seesaw
<hw>See"saw`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cause to move backward and
forward in seesaw fashion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He <qex>seesaws</qex> himself to and fro.</q> <rj><qau>Ld.
Lytton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seesaw</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Seesaw
<hw>See"saw`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Moving up and down, or to and fro;
having a reciprocating motion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seet</ent>⟦br⟧
